All Classes

  • Class Description
    CharacterCodec
    A character codec compresses strings one character at a time, assigning shorter bit sequences to more frequent characters and longer bit sequences to less frequent characters.
    CharacterFrequencies
    A helper class for building character Symbols.
    Code
    A Huffman code, having a length in bits and a value.
    Codec<Symbol>
    Interface to a compression codec, where codec stands for "Compressor / Decompressor".
    CodedSymbol<Symbol>
    An encoded symbol in a Huffman Tree, having a symbol value, a frequency and a Code.
    CsvColumn<Type>
    A typesafe model of a CSV column that belongs to a CsvSchema and can convert values for the column between strings and objects.
    CsvLine
    A model of a line in a CSV (Comma Separated Variable) file.
    CsvPropertyFilter
    A PropertyFilter that uses a CsvSchema to filter methods and fields to those whose names match columns in the schema.
    CsvReader
    Parses a stream of CSV information.
    CsvSchema
    An ordered collection of CsvColumn objects, specifying the structure of a line in a CSV (Comma Separated Data) file.
    CsvWriter
    Writes CsvLines to a PrintWriter using a given CsvSchema.
    DataCompressionKryoTypes  
    DataCompressionProject  
    DataCompressionUnitTest  
    DataFormat
    Identifying values for common data formats.
    FastHuffmanDecoder<Symbol>
    The method FastHuffmanDecoder.decode(ByteList, SymbolConsumer) decodes a string a byte at a time from the given ByteArray using a set of lookup tables built from a HuffmanCodec.
    FastHuffmanDecoder.Table<Symbol>
    A table with entries for a given prefix (or no prefix in the case of the root table).
    FastHuffmanDecoder.Table.Entry<Symbol>
    An entry in this fast decoder table
    HuffmanCharacterCodec
    Huffman compression of an entire sequence of strings using HuffmanCodec to compress individual characters in each string.
    HuffmanCharacterCodec.Converter  
    HuffmanCodec<Symbol>
    A general-purpose Huffman coder implementing Codec which works for any arbitrary symbol type.
    HuffmanStringCodec
    A Huffman compression codec where strings are treated as symbols instead of characters.
    HuffmanStringCodec.Converter  
    HuffmanStringListCodec
    Compression and decompression of lists of strings using a StringCodec and a CharacterCodec.
    Leaf<T>
    A terminal leaf in a Huffman Tree, having a symbol and a frequency.
    Node<T>
    An interior node in a Huffman tree, having a left and right sub-tree.
    StringCodec
    A string codec compresses entire strings as symbols.
    StringFrequencies
    A helper class for building string Symbols.
    StringListCodec
    A codec that compresses lists of strings.
    SymbolConsumer<Symbol>
    Consumer of a sequence of decoded symbols.
    SymbolConsumer.Directive  
    SymbolProducer<Symbol>
    A source of input symbols for a Codec to compress.
    Symbols<Symbol>
    A set of CodedSymbols, optionally including an escape symbol, that can be used to construct a HuffmanCodec.
    Tree<Symbol>
    A Huffman coding tree, composed of Node and Leaf sub-trees.
    UnquotedCsvReader
    Parses a stream of simplified CSV information.
